{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-js","path":"/sharepoint/","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"fields":{"slug":"/sharepoint/"},"id":"3e71b3db-7b27-5b1d-a5b3-435e14294be8","html":"<h1 id=\"about\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#about\" aria-label=\"about permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>About</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>we can have several sites, accessible to only our organization - e.g. a common use case is news for our team</li>\n<li>sharepoint server (older version) vs sharepoint online (newer version)</li>\n<li>site - collections of apps. apps have types</li>\n<li>sharepoint classic (older version) vs sharepoint modern (newer version)</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"document-library\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#document-library\" aria-label=\"document library permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Document Library</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>document library - a type of app that can hold documents</li>\n<li>we have a document library app called documents created by default</li>\n<li>multiple people can edit these documents at the same time (in web or by using their office-365 installed apps), and the file changes are loaded in realtime for others</li>\n<li>these documents maintain a version history of the changes</li>\n<li>when we check out a document, no one can edit it anymore, it is in read only mode for others, and only we can edit it. use case - we are restructuring the entire document, and wouldn’t want to allow others to make any changes to the document whilst we do this. after we are done with our restructuring changes, we check back in the document so that it can be edited by others again</li>\n<li>we can delete files / restore them from the recycle bin</li>\n<li>we can make the document library add a shortcut to one drive. after we do this, windows etc. os have the ability to add a microsoft account, and when we do this, the folder structure of the one drive is mimicked on our local computer. and i think all these three places, local computer, one drive and sharepoint are synced</li>\n<li>we can add templates - e.g. we want our quotes to follow a specific format. we can upload a simple excel-file with the blueprint. then, instead of clicking on Excel Workbook, people can click on Price Quote Template. this helps us establish a standard. optionally, we can click on Edit New Menu and remove the Excel Workbook option from there to kind of enforce this standard</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 210px; margin: 5px 0 5px 0 !important;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/44bd163c8edb1aaf2af114fc117eabb1/65ed1/new-menu.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 178.48101265822785%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"new menu\"\n        title=\"new menu\"\n        src=\"/static/44bd163c8edb1aaf2af114fc117eabb1/65ed1/new-menu.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/44bd163c8edb1aaf2af114fc117eabb1/c26ae/new-menu.png 158w,\n/static/44bd163c8edb1aaf2af114fc117eabb1/65ed1/new-menu.png 210w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 210px) 100vw, 210px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>traditional way of organizing documents - use folder structure, e.g. expenses from department go into expenses/department directory, from hr go into expenses/hr directory and so on. then, name files according to type of expense, e.g. suffix with _travel etc</li>\n<li>instead, we can add our own custom columns to these views. e.g. add a column of type choice, with the options as the different departments that we have. we can enable options like allow multiple option selection, set as required, etc. we can click on Edit in Grid View as well</li>\n<li>this allows us to do things like filter by departments, group by expense type, etc. easily</li>\n<li>one thing i saw - adding this metadata columns was not specific to the folder i was adding it to, it was for that entire document library. so, we should avoid folders when possible?</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; margin: 5px 0 5px 0 !important;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/554e87eab74bd93ad8f63f7c798920b7/5bf79/metadata-columns.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 29.11392405063291%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"metadata columns\"\n        title=\"metadata columns\"\n        src=\"/static/554e87eab74bd93ad8f63f7c798920b7/f058b/metadata-columns.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/554e87eab74bd93ad8f63f7c798920b7/c26ae/metadata-columns.png 158w,\n/static/554e87eab74bd93ad8f63f7c798920b7/6bdcf/metadata-columns.png 315w,\n/static/554e87eab74bd93ad8f63f7c798920b7/f058b/metadata-columns.png 630w,\n/static/554e87eab74bd93ad8f63f7c798920b7/40601/metadata-columns.png 945w,\n/static/554e87eab74bd93ad8f63f7c798920b7/5bf79/metadata-columns.png 966w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>we can add columns of type currency and then after grouping by department, click on this currency column to include aggregate by type sum, average, etc</li>\n<li>All Documents -> Format View -> Conditional Formatting. here, we add “rules” to format certain rows differently e.g. highlight row as red if the expense amount was above 500 dollars</li>\n<li>we also have two tabs - format view (to format entire rows) vs format columns (only format a specific column)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; margin: 5px 0 5px 0 !important;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/2f1d78fcfdbdf5e41ef3ecabc7f8614f/38a65/conditional-fomratting.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 31.645569620253163%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"conditional formatting\"\n        title=\"conditional formatting\"\n        src=\"/static/2f1d78fcfdbdf5e41ef3ecabc7f8614f/f058b/conditional-fomratting.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/2f1d78fcfdbdf5e41ef3ecabc7f8614f/c26ae/conditional-fomratting.png 158w,\n/static/2f1d78fcfdbdf5e41ef3ecabc7f8614f/6bdcf/conditional-fomratting.png 315w,\n/static/2f1d78fcfdbdf5e41ef3ecabc7f8614f/f058b/conditional-fomratting.png 630w,\n/static/2f1d78fcfdbdf5e41ef3ecabc7f8614f/40601/conditional-fomratting.png 945w,\n/static/2f1d78fcfdbdf5e41ef3ecabc7f8614f/38a65/conditional-fomratting.png 1075w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>views - we can save views, e.g. make some filtering, grouping, etc. and then save it, so that we can get back to it via just one click. e.g. expense team can have a particular view, review manager can have another view, etc</li>\n<li>adding our own document library - documents was a document library created by default i think. so, if we go to site contents from the side navigation and click on new, we can select list, page, document library or app. clicking on app shows us all the options of apps we can choose from, and document library is a type of app</li>\n<li>so, the idea is to add a new document library of type expenses, and then have metadata columns in it, format it according to our need using views, etc</li>\n<li>we can edit the side navigation. for e.g., our custom apps like the document library we created above will have a url, which we can add to this side navigation</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 491px; margin: 5px 0 5px 0 !important;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/362e7fd0570bf09c54183dacd3304dd1/13566/add-new-app-edit-side-nav.drawio.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 86.70886075949367%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"add new app edit side nav\"\n        title=\"add new app edit side nav\"\n        src=\"/static/362e7fd0570bf09c54183dacd3304dd1/13566/add-new-app-edit-side-nav.drawio.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/362e7fd0570bf09c54183dacd3304dd1/c26ae/add-new-app-edit-side-nav.drawio.png 158w,\n/static/362e7fd0570bf09c54183dacd3304dd1/6bdcf/add-new-app-edit-side-nav.drawio.png 315w,\n/static/362e7fd0570bf09c54183dacd3304dd1/13566/add-new-app-edit-side-nav.drawio.png 491w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 491px) 100vw, 491px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>we can go to library settings from the gear icon in the top right. this helps us set things like versioning related configuration, some formulas for validations, etc</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"pages\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#pages\" aria-label=\"pages permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Pages</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>pages are like a mosaic of different apps?\n<ul>\n<li>wiki page - most customizable, on the way to be deprecated</li>\n<li>site page - have templates to make our job easier - this is encouraged to be used</li>\n<li>web part page - deprecated older version</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>we can insert document libraries in pages (e.g. a view of the expense library), embed code in pages, etc</li>\n<li>subsites - a tree like structure for sites, e.g. we can have different subsites under a site for different departments like marketing, management, etc. hub sites are now encouraged over subsites</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"lists\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#lists\" aria-label=\"lists permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Lists</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>sharepoint lists - way of managing data</li>\n<li>a document library is like a list, where each row corresponds to a document</li>\n<li>we can create list from site content -> new -> list</li>\n<li>we can create a blank list, create a list from an existing list, or create a list from excel</li>\n<li>tip - when creating a list from excel, ensure that the data in excel is formatted as a table. now, when creating a list from it, we can select the table that sharepoint should use when creating this list</li>\n<li>every sharepoint list should have one column as title - like a primary key. i think it should it be unique</li>\n<li>we can edit lists using the grid view or using the normal view, where a form side panel pops up</li>\n<li>we can select multiple rows, and setting a value for a column sets it for all of them, e.g. we can change status from todo to in progress for selected items in a list</li>\n<li>we can modify the edit form side panel as well - select / hide what fields should and shouldn’t be shown, modify the order they appear in inside the form, etc - click on + New -> Edit Form -> Edit columns</li>\n<li>each item has its own view page as well, which for e.g. can be shared with others for effective collaboration</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; margin: 5px 0 5px 0 !important;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/642a5727965e221b0f447e757cd8cf52/ea7fb/display-item.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 38.60759493670886%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"display item\"\n        title=\"display item\"\n        src=\"/static/642a5727965e221b0f447e757cd8cf52/f058b/display-item.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/642a5727965e221b0f447e757cd8cf52/c26ae/display-item.png 158w,\n/static/642a5727965e221b0f447e757cd8cf52/6bdcf/display-item.png 315w,\n/static/642a5727965e221b0f447e757cd8cf52/f058b/display-item.png 630w,\n/static/642a5727965e221b0f447e757cd8cf52/ea7fb/display-item.png 788w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>lists can have a column of type choice - it can have multi select, and even allow adding of custom values not present in the list of choices we configured</li>\n<li>we can have columns of type person. my understanding - this can take values from the people in our organization (the 25 free licenses i saw when creating my developer account), e.g. sales coverage</li>\n<li>calculated columns - add column -> see all column types -> next -> fill appropriate values</li>\n<li>so, calculated columns are available only in the older experience</li>\n<li>i couldn’t see column settings for calculated column, is it because it was created in the older experience? e.g. i wanted to check the “friendly format” option for a new calculated column reward period end</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 458px; margin: 5px 0 5px 0 !important;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/96e159c1c81e3e7e80bfe2b22561017c/f7a31/calculated-column.drawio.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 113.9240506329114%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"calculated column\"\n        title=\"calculated column\"\n        src=\"/static/96e159c1c81e3e7e80bfe2b22561017c/f7a31/calculated-column.drawio.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/96e159c1c81e3e7e80bfe2b22561017c/c26ae/calculated-column.drawio.png 158w,\n/static/96e159c1c81e3e7e80bfe2b22561017c/6bdcf/calculated-column.drawio.png 315w,\n/static/96e159c1c81e3e7e80bfe2b22561017c/f7a31/calculated-column.drawio.png 458w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 458px) 100vw, 458px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>lookup columns - when we create a column as a lookup column, it can take values from another list - a dropdown will come up, with items the same as for e.g. the title of the list we chose. we can also add additional columns from this list, which auto populate based on the option we chose for the lookup column</li>\n<li>the values in the lookup columns are hyperlinks to the actual view</li>\n<li>e.g. we choose repair shop, and repair shop city and repair shop speciality get populated automatically</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; margin: 5px 0 5px 0 !important;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4927d12c6e9b79aae0b8c0033ec95702/a0730/lookup-column.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 18.354430379746837%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"lookup column\"\n        title=\"lookup column\"\n        src=\"/static/4927d12c6e9b79aae0b8c0033ec95702/f058b/lookup-column.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4927d12c6e9b79aae0b8c0033ec95702/c26ae/lookup-column.png 158w,\n/static/4927d12c6e9b79aae0b8c0033ec95702/6bdcf/lookup-column.png 315w,\n/static/4927d12c6e9b79aae0b8c0033ec95702/f058b/lookup-column.png 630w,\n/static/4927d12c6e9b79aae0b8c0033ec95702/40601/lookup-column.png 945w,\n/static/4927d12c6e9b79aae0b8c0033ec95702/a0730/lookup-column.png 1131w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>we can add comments (like on blog posts) to each item in sharepoint lists. e.g. notes for a specific client</li>\n<li>sharepoint lists have versions too (at item level)</li>\n<li>recall how we modified edit forms - (+ New -> Edit form -> Edit columns). here, we can show a field based on a condition. e.g. if shop type is affiliated, show the affiliate shop name, otherwise do not. when we click on the ellipsis dropdown, we get the option of edit conditional formula. there, we can set the formula to, for instance <code class=\"language-text\">=if([$ShopType] == 'Afiliated', 'true', 'false')</code> <a href=\"https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/sharepoint/dev/declarative-customization/list-form-conditional-show-hide#specify-conditional-formula-to-show-or-hide-columns\">docs</a></li>\n<li>we can also add helpful descriptions to fields (Column Settings -> Edit) so that when users are presented with the new / edit form for an item, they see that description before making any modifications</li>\n<li>row level validation - sharepoint runs a script everytime a new row is added / edited and returns an error accordingly. to do this, Settings -> List Settings -> Validation Settings\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre style=\"counter-reset: linenumber NaN\" class=\"language-text line-numbers\"><code class=\"language-text\">=OR(\n  AND([Afiliate Shop Name] &lt;> \"\", [Shop Type] = \"Afiliated\"),\n  AND([Afiliate Shop Name] = \"\", [Is Afiliated] = \"Not Afiliated\")\n)</code><span aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"line-numbers-rows\" style=\"white-space: normal; width: auto; left: 0;\"><span></span><span></span><span></span><span></span></span></pre></div>\nit allows us to provide a helpful validation message to display as well if the validation fails</li>\n<li>we can create calendar views based on a column or some columns</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; margin: 5px 0 5px 0 !important;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/98d15b22359c26b6a94d536db8a06ecc/78612/calendar-view.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 22.78481012658228%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"calendar view\"\n        title=\"calendar view\"\n        src=\"/static/98d15b22359c26b6a94d536db8a06ecc/f058b/calendar-view.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/98d15b22359c26b6a94d536db8a06ecc/c26ae/calendar-view.png 158w,\n/static/98d15b22359c26b6a94d536db8a06ecc/6bdcf/calendar-view.png 315w,\n/static/98d15b22359c26b6a94d536db8a06ecc/f058b/calendar-view.png 630w,\n/static/98d15b22359c26b6a94d536db8a06ecc/40601/calendar-view.png 945w,\n/static/98d15b22359c26b6a94d536db8a06ecc/78612/calendar-view.png 1260w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>alerts - selected people, dl, etc. receive an alert if an item changes. it can be done at item level or at the list level as well. e.g. we have a coverage employee for a particular client. we can configure it so that instead of getting alerts on every change, we get a summary of changes daily</li>\n<li>my understanding of exporting to excel vs exporting to csv - exporting to excel means excel is still connected to sharepoint, can receive updates to sharepoint automatically, etc</li>\n<li>deleted items go to recycle bin as well, so they can be restored</li>\n</ul>\n<h1 id=\"permissions\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#permissions\" aria-label=\"permissions permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Permissions</h1>\n<ul>\n<li>permissions = authorization != authentication</li>\n<li>groups = collection of users. groups called owners, members and visitors exist by default, though we can create custom groups as well apart from these</li>\n<li>we assign levels to a group. levels are a collection of permissions. the 5 levels present by default are full control, design, edit, contribute and read, though we can create custom levels as well</li>\n<li>we can set levels on a user directly, but this should be avoided</li>\n<li>users can be a part of multiple groups / permissions can be a part of multiple levels</li>\n<li>subsites inherit permissions from sites, but we can break this inheritance if we want to (should be avoided as this can make managing very difficult very soon)</li>\n<li>permission cascading - rarely used, permissions of subsites are combined to form the permissions of the site</li>\n<li>Settings -> Site Permissions -> Advanced permissions settings</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; margin: 5px 0 5px 0 !important;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d265b6db4bbb75fd7409c055da9c69a0/2c288/permissions.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 19.62025316455696%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"permissions\"\n        title=\"permissions\"\n        src=\"/static/d265b6db4bbb75fd7409c055da9c69a0/f058b/permissions.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d265b6db4bbb75fd7409c055da9c69a0/c26ae/permissions.png 158w,\n/static/d265b6db4bbb75fd7409c055da9c69a0/6bdcf/permissions.png 315w,\n/static/d265b6db4bbb75fd7409c055da9c69a0/f058b/permissions.png 630w,\n/static/d265b6db4bbb75fd7409c055da9c69a0/2c288/permissions.png 684w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>from ms 365 admin center, i selected all the users except myself (admin) and hit on reset password and checked the option to send the users and their passwords to my admin account email</li>\n<li>inside advanced permission settings, click on grant permissions, and then enter users and the group they should be added to (again do not add levels directly)</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 531px; margin: 5px 0 5px 0 !important;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6f252e30bec1b9a8fd8340091bbe22cb/d4713/grant-permissions.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.9620253164557%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"grant permissions\"\n        title=\"grant permissions\"\n        src=\"/static/6f252e30bec1b9a8fd8340091bbe22cb/d4713/grant-permissions.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6f252e30bec1b9a8fd8340091bbe22cb/c26ae/grant-permissions.png 158w,\n/static/6f252e30bec1b9a8fd8340091bbe22cb/6bdcf/grant-permissions.png 315w,\n/static/6f252e30bec1b9a8fd8340091bbe22cb/d4713/grant-permissions.png 531w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 531px) 100vw, 531px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>select the users by clicking on checkbox -> Actions -> Remove Users from Group</li>\n<li>go to Advanced permission settings -> Permission Levels from the top menu bar -> Add a Permission Level -> select the permissions which we would like to add to this level</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; margin: 5px 0 5px 0 !important;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6a83978584ae2a96e8d9896f99ddf770/aa61c/add-level.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 53.16455696202532%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"add level\"\n        title=\"add level\"\n        src=\"/static/6a83978584ae2a96e8d9896f99ddf770/f058b/add-level.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6a83978584ae2a96e8d9896f99ddf770/c26ae/add-level.png 158w,\n/static/6a83978584ae2a96e8d9896f99ddf770/6bdcf/add-level.png 315w,\n/static/6a83978584ae2a96e8d9896f99ddf770/f058b/add-level.png 630w,\n/static/6a83978584ae2a96e8d9896f99ddf770/40601/add-level.png 945w,\n/static/6a83978584ae2a96e8d9896f99ddf770/aa61c/add-level.png 1065w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>now, we create a group and add permissions to it</li>\n<li>when users don’t have access to a specific site in sharepoint, they see an access denied screen, and they can click on the request access button on this screen. on doing this, they see the following page</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; margin: 5px 0 5px 0 !important;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/69f229eb2b835c5bf528bf25dc27f88d/4e6ec/request-access.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 44.30379746835443%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"request access\"\n        title=\"request access\"\n        src=\"/static/69f229eb2b835c5bf528bf25dc27f88d/f058b/request-access.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/69f229eb2b835c5bf528bf25dc27f88d/c26ae/request-access.png 158w,\n/static/69f229eb2b835c5bf528bf25dc27f88d/6bdcf/request-access.png 315w,\n/static/69f229eb2b835c5bf528bf25dc27f88d/f058b/request-access.png 630w,\n/static/69f229eb2b835c5bf528bf25dc27f88d/4e6ec/request-access.png 827w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<ul>\n<li>this triggers an email to the admin with actionable links</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 630px; margin: 5px 0 5px 0 !important;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/f4692459bd671dbacd11feda4005c83c/99272/request-access-email.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 63.92405063291139%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"request access email\"\n        title=\"request access email\"\n        src=\"/static/f4692459bd671dbacd11feda4005c83c/f058b/request-access-email.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/f4692459bd671dbacd11feda4005c83c/c26ae/request-access-email.png 158w,\n/static/f4692459bd671dbacd11feda4005c83c/6bdcf/request-access-email.png 315w,\n/static/f4692459bd671dbacd11feda4005c83c/f058b/request-access-email.png 630w,\n/static/f4692459bd671dbacd11feda4005c83c/99272/request-access-email.png 669w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 630px) 100vw, 630px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Sharepoint"}}},"pageContext":{"id":"3e71b3db-7b27-5b1d-a5b3-435e14294be8"}},"staticQueryHashes":["1037383464","1617985380"]}